My
father
began
life
in
the
profession
which
your
uncle,
Mr.
Phillips,
appears
to
do
so
much
credit
to
but
he
gave
up
everything
to
be
of
use
to
the
late
Mr.
Darcy
and
devoted
all
his
time
to
the
care
of
the
Pemberley
property.
He
was
most
highly
esteemed
by
Mr.
Darcy,
a
most
intimate,
confidential
friend.
Mr.
Darcy
often
acknowledged
himself
to
be
under
the
greatest
obligations
to
my
father's
active
superintendence,
and
when,
immediately
