"What
sort
of
girl
is
Miss
Darcy?"
He
shook
his
head.
"I
wish
I
could
call
her
amiable.
It
gives
me
pain
to
speak
ill
of
a
Darcy.
But
she
is
too
much
like
her
brother
very,
very
proud.
As
a
child,
she
was
affectionate
and
pleasing,
and
extremely
fond
of
me;
and
I
have
devoted
hours
and
